   <body>
      <p>Customer Incentive Manager is built on the Apttus OMNI™ platform. Customer Incentive Manager enables companies to manage customer incentive strategies and programs. It can be used to set up price incentive programs such as Billing Programs. These programs share common structures and common processes.</p>
      <p>The common definition, structures, and templates for Customer Incentive Programs are:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>Header</li>
         <li>Scope</li>
         <li>Qualifications &amp; Benefits</li>
         <li>Multiple Qualifications &amp; Benefits</li>
         <li>Participants</li>
         <li>Schedule</li>
         <li>Import</li>
         <li>Adding products</li>
         <li>On-Demand Validations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Common processes for price incentive programs are:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>Approval Workflows</li>
         <li>Program and Settlement Lifecycle Management</li>
         <li>Bucketing and Calculations<p>
               <fig>
                  <image placement="break"
                         width="600"
                         href="../attachments/102432687/109936712.png"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>Apttus Customer Incentive Manager allows a user to perform the following tasks:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>Program Manager component<ul>
               <li>Create an account or product-specific programs.</li>
               <li>Update and align program qualifications.</li>
               <li>Create programs from other programs.</li>
               <li>Manage program lifecycles.</li>
            </ul>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
         <li>Month End Billing Program<ul>
               <li>Scope</li>
               <li>Adding Products</li>
               <li>Qualifications and Benefits</li>
               <li>Participants</li>
               <li>Schedule</li>
            </ul>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <ul>
         <li>Reward Saving Program<ul>
               <li>Scope</li>
               <li>Qualifications and Benefits<ul>
                     <li>Multiple Qualifications and Benefits (Volume Tier)</li>
                     <li>Multiple Qualifications and Benefits (Revenue Tier)</li>
                  </ul>
               </li>
               <li>Participants</li>
               <li>Schedule</li>
            </ul>
         </li>
         <li>Bundle Saving Program<ul>
               <li>Scope</li>
               <li>Qualifications and Benefits</li>
               <li>Participants</li>
               <li>Schedule</li>
               <li>Importing Benefit Line Items</li>
            </ul>
         </li>
         <li>Package Saving Program<ul>
               <li>Scope</li>
               <li>Qualifications and Benefits</li>
               <li>Participants</li>
               <li>Schedule</li>
               <li>Primary and Secondary Packages</li>
            </ul>
         </li>
         <li>Adding Predefined Product Groups to Programs</li>
         <li>Duplicating Sections</li>
         <li>On-Demand Validations</li>
      </ul>
